modules.description: The module provides operations to parse, validate, and manipulate cron expressions and crontabs, including constructing field-specific values (like `All` or `List`), serializing entries to strings, and managing system crontabs. It works with structured representations of scheduled tasks (`Cron.entry`) and full cron tables (`Cron.t`), enabling use cases like programmatically adding recurring jobs or validating time-based triggers for task execution.
